data.content:
All three code snippets hit EF Core 10 breaking changes. Here's what breaks and the fixes:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` ŌĆö expression tree no longer compiles

EF 10 changed the parameter from `Expression<Func<...>>` to `Func<...>`, so manually built expression trees won't compile. The fix is dramatically simpler:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

No more `Expression.Lambda` / `Expression.Call` ŌĆö just use regular C# control flow inside the lambda.

---

### 2. Complex type column names ŌĆö two breaking changes

**a) Shared-name columns are now uniquified.** `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously shared one `Street` column; EF 10 appends a number (`Street`, `Street1`). To keep the old behavior, pin column names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});
```

**b) Nested complex types now use the full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was previously mapped to column `BillingAddress_City`; EF 10 maps it to `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. To preserve the old name:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

> **Tip:** If you have an existing database, generate a migration after upgrading and inspect it ŌĆö any unintended column renames will be visible.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` ŌĆö new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter (for redacted SQL logging). Add it to your signatures:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ŌåÉ new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (sensitive data redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual execution SQL
    }
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
